{
  "doc_id": "49027",
  "text": "A three-dimensional computational model of Galway Bay had been developed previously. A bathymetric model of the Galway Bay was developed using data from the Integrated Mapping for the Sustainable Development of Ireland's Marine Resource (INFOMAR) program. The deepest area is approximately 70 m near the south west corner of the open boundaries. The mean water depth in the domain is 30.7 m. Tidal elevation for boundary conditions obtained from the Oregon Tide Prediction Software (OTPS), wind data obtained from the Europe Centre for Mid-Range Weather Forecasts (ECMWF) and River Corrib flow data provided by the Irish Open Public Work (OPW) were used to drive the models. Detailed EFDC modeling setup for Galway Bay such as wind forcing and vertical layer structure is described in Ren et al. [CITATION_1] , O'Donncha et al. [CITATION_2] and Ren et al. [CITATION_3] . ",
